File: Power structure Pixabay/Cocoparisienne JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will be implementing load reduction in the Limpopo and Mpumalanga province to avoid network overloading in high-density areas. The power utility said load reduction will take place between 5 pm and 9 pm. READ: Ramaphosa: Eskom steadily improving Areas like Mopani District, and Ehlanzeni District will be affected by the load reduction. Provincial statements issued by Eskom name the specific areas that will be experiencing power cuts. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
